# YT Agent — Colab Secrets
#
# Add these in Colab's 🔑 Secrets panel (toggle "Notebook access" ON for
# each). Everything else (NIM, Groq, Pexels, HuggingFace, storage
# credentials...) lives in the dashboard's database and is pulled at
# worker startup.

# ── REQUIRED (Coolify + Pocketbase deployment) ─────────────────
# Your dashboard URL — used by the worker to register + poll for jobs.
COOLIFY_BASE_URL              https://yt-agent.thyker.online

# Pocketbase URL = COOLIFY_BASE_URL + /pb (just append /pb).
PB_URL                        https://yt-agent.thyker.online/pb

# Pocketbase superuser email + password (created via the install URL
# you used when first booting Pocketbase).
POCKETBASE_ADMIN_EMAIL        admin@yt-agent.thyker.online
POCKETBASE_ADMIN_PASSWORD     your-strong-password-here

# Shared secret for dashboard maintenance routes — must match the
# RENDER_TRIGGER_KEY env var on your Coolify deployment.
RENDER_TRIGGER_KEY            <32-byte hex from openssl rand -hex 32>

# Encryption key for storage provider credentials stored in Pocketbase.
# Must match STORAGE_PROVIDERS_ENC_KEY on the Coolify side OR the
# worker can't decrypt MinIO/R2/S3 credentials.
STORAGE_PROVIDERS_ENC_KEY     <32-byte hex — same value as Coolify>

# ── OPTIONAL — Worker identity ─────────────────────────────────
INSTANCE_LABEL                colab-gpu        # shown in the dashboard
INSTANCE_TIER                 gpu              # gpu = preferred, cpu = fallback

# ── LEGACY (only if your dashboard is still on Vercel + Firestore + R2) ─
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS_JSON   { "type": "service_account", ... }
# R2_ACCOUNT_ID / R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID / R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY / R2_BUCKET / R2_PUBLIC_URL
# SFTP_HOST / SFTP_PORT / SFTP_USER / SFTP_PASS / SFTP_BASE_DIR / PUBLIC_BASE_URL
